      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs documented with sources; uncertain inputs identified and distributions assigned for Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "All 13 model inputs documented including blood viscosity, density, pump geometry tolerances, and boundary conditions. Uncertain inputs assigned probability distributions based on manufacturer tolerances and literature. Monte Carlo UQ propagated these distributions through the model to produce output uncertainty bounds on RH. Achieved level meets MRL 2 requirement. Note: the Monte Carlo analysis quantifies total output variance; characterization of which individual inputs contribute most to output variability was not separately pursued as a sensitivity decomposition exercise."
